Create a new GitHub Personal Access Token (classic) with appropriate scopes:

Go to your GitHub Settings > Developer Settings > Personal access tokens > Tokens (classic)

Click Generate new token (classic)

Select scopes: repo, workflow (at least)

Generate and copy the new token — you won’t be able to see it again after leaving the page!








aws ssm put-parameter --name "/github/pat/sports-commerce" --value "ghp_NEWLY_GENERATED_TOKEN" --type SecureString --overwrite


Run Terraform again 


